  "name": "Colorectal Cancer - Comprehensive Provider Query (DX + Meds + Procedures + Labs)",
  "description": "Simulates a medical oncologist identifying their complete CRC patient population. Combines: CRC diagnosis codes, chemotherapy regimens, colonoscopy procedures, and elevated CEA. **First test case unioning Condition + MedicationRequest + Procedure + Observation in a single multi-query test.** Tests four-resource-type union.",
  "prompt": "I need to identify my complete colorectal cancer patient population for a quality improvement initiative on chemotherapy adherence and surveillance. From clinical experience, CRC patients are documented in different ways: most have a formal diagnosis (often anatomic-location-specific), most are on chemotherapy regimens (5-FU, capecitabine, oxaliplatin, irinotecan, leucovorin), most have undergone colonoscopy for diagnosis, and many have elevated CEA on surveillance.\n\nPlease run multiple FHIR queries to capture the full population:\n1. Patients with any colorectal cancer diagnosis (colon, cecum, rectum, primary colon, descending colon)\n2. Patients prescribed CRC chemotherapy (5-FU, capecitabine, oxaliplatin, irinotecan, leucovorin)\n3. Patients who have undergone colonoscopy\n4. Patients with elevated CEA (>5 ng/mL)\n\nFor each query, return the matching resources. I want the union of all patients found.",
